{"article_id":"noxshHF8TLg0GTER","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"New Reports Of Chemical Weapons In Syria ;","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Many May Be Dead","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"( We most recently updated this post at 9:10 a.m . ET . )","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"`` Two Syrian pro-opposition groups are claiming","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"that dozens of people were killed Wednesday in a poisonous gas attack near Damascus , ''","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"NPR 's Jean Cochran reported earlier this morning on our Newscast .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"The groups are blaming the attack on government forces ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"`` The reports have not been independently confirmed , ''","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Jean added ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"and President Bashar Assad 's regime says","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"the claims are `` baseless . ''","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"Reuters began Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"leading its report this way :","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"`` Syrian activists accused President Bashar al-Assad 's forces of launching a nerve gas attack","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that killed at least 213 people on Wednesday ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"in what would ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"if confirmed ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"be by far the worst reported use of poison gas in the two-year-old civil war . ''","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"Shortly after 9 a.m . ET , the wire service said","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"activists were claiming","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"that nearly 500 people had died .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"`` If confirmed , ''","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Reuters added ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"it would be `` by far the worst reported use of chemical arms in the two-year-old civil war . ''","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"This news comes","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"as a U.N. team is in Syria","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"to investigate earlier alleged uses of chemical weapons .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"The BBC 's Naomi Grimley adds","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that opposition groups have released `` distressing pictures","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"[ that ]","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"show children","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"lying limp in the arms of adults ''","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"and adults","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"being hosed down ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"allegedly to wash away chemicals .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"she says ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"those images have n't been independently verified .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"According to CNN ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"`` the explosions took place in eastern and western Ghouta , rebel strongholds","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"that the regime has for more than a year been desperately trying to take back .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"They do n't want rebels pushing into the capital . ''","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"British Foreign Secretary William Hague says in a statement","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"released by his office","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"that he is `` deeply concerned by reports","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"that hundreds of people ,","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"including children ,","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"have been killed in airstrikes and a chemical weapons attack on rebel-held areas near Damascus . '' `` These reports are uncorroborated","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"and we are urgently seeking more information .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"But it is clear","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"if they are verified ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"it would mark a shocking escalation in the use of chemical weapons in Syria .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"Those","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"who order the use of chemical weapons ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"and those","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"who use them ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"should be in no doubt","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"that we will work in every way","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"we can","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"to hold them to account .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"I call on the Syrian Government to allow immediate access to the area for the UN team","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"currently investigating previous allegations of chemical weapons use .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"The U.K. will be raising this incident at the UN Security Council . ''","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Since early 2011 ,","depth":4},{"id":66,"text":"when protests against the Assad regime began ,","depth":4},{"id":67,"text":"Syria has slid into what 's now effectively a civil war .","depth":4},{"id":68,"text":"About 100,000 people have died , many of them civilians ,","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"the U.N. estimates .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":139,"left":71,"right":138,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":71,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":133,"right":137,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":2,"right":132,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":132,"left":95,"right":131,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":92,"right":94,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":79,"right":91,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":79,"left":75,"right":78,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":73,"right":74,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":72,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":72,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":74,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":78,"left":76,"right":77,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":76,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":10,"right":11,"relat